The trial starts tomorrow.

00:08.685 --> 00:12.207
I can bring you up to speed on it.
The facts are straightforward.

00:12.207 --> 00:13.774
And why can't Tara do it?

00:13.774 --> 00:15.994
Well, Tara's a junior associate.

00:15.994 --> 00:18.698
This trial's gonna be in the news.
It's hardly the kind of case that…

00:18.698 --> 00:23.248
Brad, it isn't the case 
so much as it is the client, right?

00:23.391 --> 00:27.261
And it isn't who she is
so much as what she is, right?

00:28.630 --> 00:30.967
What is she, Brad?

00:31.647 --> 00:33.434
Can't you even say the word?

00:33.434 --> 00:35.834
–I can say it.
–Well, what is she, Brad?

00:37.338 --> 00:39.418
She's a…

00:39.418 --> 00:40.860
homosexual.

00:40.860 --> 00:44.423
And what's the word
for a female homosexual?

00:44.423 --> 00:45.841
–Lesbian.
–I couldn't really hear that.

00:45.841 --> 00:47.119
She's a lesbian!

00:48.391 --> 00:50.686
You don't want to do the case
because your client's a lesbian.

00:50.686 --> 00:52.776
Lori, this is a high-profile case.

00:52.776 --> 00:56.859
I have worked my entire life to associate 
with decency and what is good for America.

00:56.859 --> 00:58.370
And lesbians are bad for America.

00:58.370 --> 00:59.778
They have bad values.

00:59.778 --> 01:01.241
Reflects poorly on all of us.

01:01.241 --> 01:03.293
As a nation.

01:05.756 --> 01:08.843
Now, would you like to 
tell me the real reason?

01:14.586 --> 01:15.398
What do you mean?

01:15.398 --> 01:18.534
I know for a fact you've
represented gay clients before.

01:18.534 --> 01:20.335
Not on television, not in the news.

01:20.335 --> 01:22.391
Brad, we're friends.

01:22.391 --> 01:24.238
Level with me.

01:24.238 --> 01:27.226
What is it about this 
particular lesbian?

01:30.769 --> 01:33.093
I'm attracted to her.

