02:15.123 --> 02:17.183
Some of us have trials today,

02:17.183 --> 02:18.400
so if you don't mind,
I'd like to cut out.

02:18.400 --> 02:21.276
What's your case about, Brad?

02:23.424 --> 02:26.326
What is it about?

02:27.913 --> 02:31.069
It involves interference
with contractual relations.

02:31.069 --> 02:32.757
You mean…

02:32.757 --> 02:35.443
lesbians.

02:35.899 --> 02:37.864
Where are you?

02:37.864 --> 02:40.693
Today they're calling Tracey to 
testify that her ex-lover was…

02:40.693 --> 02:43.257
lesbian ex-lover.

02:43.257 --> 02:46.031
To testify that Tracey was
scamming her for money.

02:46.031 --> 02:50.308
Tracey was, in fact,
not an actual bona fide…

02:50.308 --> 02:51.767
lesbian?

02:51.767 --> 02:53.226
–You like saying it.
–I do.

02:53.226 --> 02:54.357
–Say it again.
–Lesbian.

02:54.357 --> 02:58.436
–Keep going.
–Lesbian, lesbian…

02:58.662 --> 03:00.298
lesbian.

03:00.298 --> 03:01.641
All together now.

03:01.641 --> 03:03.046
Lesbian.

03:03.046 --> 03:04.722
I also like to watch.
How many people are lesbian?

03:04.722 --> 03:07.114
All right, that's enough.
This is a staff meeting.

03:07.114 --> 03:11.771
I'll ask you all to conduct yourselves
appropriately and professionally.

03:11.771 --> 03:13.800
Cookies, everyone.

03:13.800 --> 03:16.342
Nourishment is most important
in the morning.

03:16.342 --> 03:18.547
–Who is this woman?
–Take two, Tara.

03:18.547 --> 03:20.845
–You're a rail.
–Who is this woman?

03:20.845 --> 03:22.941
The ones on the left have a little bran

03:22.941 --> 03:25.414
to help our older lawyers
with their routine.

03:25.414 --> 03:27.702
Who is this woman?

03:27.702 --> 03:30.946
I'm Catherine Piper.
I'm Alan's new assistant.

03:30.946 --> 03:33.193
My, don't you have an interesting face.

03:33.193 --> 03:35.323
We are in the middle of a staff meeting.

03:35.323 --> 03:37.310
No need to be snippy, dear,

03:37.310 --> 03:39.648
especially since
I come bearing treats.

03:39.648 --> 03:43.313
You never get a second chance
to make a first impression.

03:43.313 --> 03:45.239
You certainly make one…

03:45.239 --> 03:46.643
with all that bleach.

03:46.643 --> 03:48.988
Ma'am, you will have to leave.

03:48.988 --> 03:52.016
I'm beginning to not like you.

03:52.016 --> 03:55.060
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have a trial myself.

03:55.312 --> 03:56.829
You have a trial?

03:56.829 --> 03:58.185
Yes, tomorrow morning.

03:58.185 --> 04:01.229
–I've got to go meet with my client.
–What kind of trial?

04:01.229 --> 04:03.015
Criminal.

04:03.015 --> 04:06.646
It's a doctor who did…

04:06.646 --> 04:09.321
something against the law.

04:10.378 --> 04:13.000
Who else is with you
on this trial?

04:13.000 --> 04:15.882
Nobody. I decided to fly solo.

04:15.882 --> 04:17.632
Think about that.

04:17.632 --> 04:19.332
Tell Shirley.

04:19.332 --> 04:23.038
Denny Crane without a co-pilot.

04:28.615 --> 04:30.797
Dear God in heaven.

04:41.793 --> 04:42.924
Shirley.

04:42.924 --> 04:45.033
–Alan.
–You're in the men's room again.

04:45.033 --> 04:45.995
I need a favor.

04:45.995 --> 04:47.836
Certainly. My stall or yours?

04:47.836 --> 04:49.345
Driving into work this morning,

04:49.345 --> 04:52.795
I heard of a trial involving
this new wonder diet drug.

04:52.795 --> 04:55.724
The drug, and accordingly the trial,
are making the news,

04:55.724 --> 04:57.963
and then I heard something 
very disturbing.

04:57.963 --> 05:00.293
The name of the lawyer
handling the defense.

05:00.293 --> 05:04.043
Denny Crane. –Nobody wants 
this firm held up to ridicule.

05:04.043 --> 05:07.369
Nobody wants Denny exposed.

05:07.369 --> 05:08.712
I've been in court with Denny.

05:08.712 --> 05:11.845
He knows what he's doing
at least 50% of the time.

05:11.845 --> 05:14.029
I like him, you like him.

05:14.029 --> 05:16.261
I have to be in New York.

05:18.469 --> 05:21.618
If she tries to pee standing up,
come and get me.

05:27.796 --> 05:29.628
Lock and load.

05:37.469 --> 05:39.811
Tracey, we can still
make this go away.

05:39.811 --> 05:42.056
How many times must 
you both say that?

05:42.056 --> 05:43.251
Until you consider it.

05:43.251 --> 05:45.862
Are you sure you want your personal 
life probed with details at 11:00?

05:45.862 --> 05:47.207
I didn't steal from her,

05:47.207 --> 05:50.156
and I won't offer her
anything to settle.

05:50.156 --> 05:52.010
I'd appreciate you
being on my side.

05:52.010 --> 05:54.236
–Hey, we're on your side.
–All right.

05:56.262 --> 05:59.352
We met at an AIDS fundraiser
about two years ago.

05:59.352 --> 06:02.914
We were both publicists,
so we had a lot in common.

06:02.914 --> 06:06.430
And at some point, Ms Rogers,
you and the defendant became lovers?

06:06.430 --> 06:08.899
Yes. She moved into my home.

06:08.899 --> 06:12.135
Ultimately, we became business partners
and formed Rogers and Green,

06:12.135 --> 06:15.307
which became one of the top 
P.R. firms in Boston.

06:15.307 --> 06:16.305
And what happened?

06:16.305 --> 06:20.101
Well, quite simply, after she gained
access to my files and my clients,

06:20.101 --> 06:21.836
–she stole them.
–Objection.

06:21.836 --> 06:22.988
Sustained.

06:22.988 --> 06:26.833
I since learned that she's not even gay,
that she basically pretended to be

06:26.833 --> 06:29.699
so that she could gain access
to my client roster.

06:29.699 --> 06:32.920
Now, Ms Rogers, when you allege
that the defendant pretended to be gay…

06:32.920 --> 06:36.025
She had boyfriends 
before me and one after.

06:36.025 --> 06:39.183
Perhaps that makes her bisexual.
It doesn't make any difference,

06:39.183 --> 06:42.955
because I specifically asked her that
at the beginning of our relationship.

06:42.955 --> 06:45.203
–Whether she was bisexual.
–Yes.

06:45.203 --> 06:48.430
I'd been hurt before by 
heterosexual women experimenting,

06:48.430 --> 06:51.150
and I didn't want to 
go down that road again.

06:51.150 --> 06:53.206
She told me she was gay.

06:53.206 --> 06:57.413
That was a lie, one that 
cost me valuable clients.

06:57.413 --> 06:59.077
Just let me understand this.

06:59.077 --> 07:02.185
The basis of your claim is that my
client faked her sexual orientation

07:02.185 --> 07:04.084
for the sole purpose of getting you
to fall in love with her

07:04.084 --> 07:07.723
so she could move into your home
and business and steal your clients.

07:07.723 --> 07:10.229
Yes. –When, in fact, it wasn't
only your business.

07:10.229 --> 07:12.232
You built it up together
over the two years.

07:12.232 --> 07:13.647
I founded the company,

07:13.647 --> 07:17.012
and most of the clients
that she left with were mine.

07:17.012 --> 07:21.772
Now, Ms Rogers, as business partners, 
as a couple, you two were quite prominent.

07:21.772 --> 07:25.606
Isn't that right? Your photos were constantly
in the “Globe” or “Boston” magazine,

07:25.606 --> 07:27.778
being called the new “it girls”.

07:27.778 --> 07:29.771
You two got more publicity
than your clients.

07:29.771 --> 07:31.592
It worked to the clients' 
benefit as well,

07:31.592 --> 07:33.164
so I don't see your point.

07:33.164 --> 07:36.106
Well, my point is that you two got 
a lot of publicity together as a couple.

07:36.106 --> 07:38.072
Business just went through the roof.

07:38.072 --> 07:41.152
Even if you were defrauded, it wasn't 
exactly to your financial detriment.

07:41.152 --> 07:43.325
It was certainly to my 
detriment when she left.

07:43.325 --> 07:45.576
Well, but even so, 
you make more money now than you

07:45.576 --> 07:49.002
did before even meeting Tracey,
so how could you have been hurt?

07:49.002 --> 07:51.161
How have I been hurt?

07:51.161 --> 07:53.829
She caused me to fall in love
with her. That…

07:53.829 --> 07:57.983
That's what this is really about,
isn't it, Ms Rogers?

07:57.983 --> 08:01.482
This isn't a business dispute.
This is a domestic one.

08:01.482 --> 08:03.852
–Did she break your heart?
–Objection.

08:04.029 --> 08:06.062
I'll allow it.

08:06.729 --> 08:09.010
Did she break your heart?

08:12.193 --> 08:13.622
Yes.

08:15.541 --> 08:18.357
You were in love with her.

08:21.143 --> 08:23.494
Now, Ms Rogers…

08:23.578 --> 08:27.283
during the two years that you 
were together with my client,

08:27.283 --> 08:29.989
do you feel that she 
was in love with you?

08:35.846 --> 08:38.207
Yes.

08:39.696 --> 08:42.193
Obviously, should I get 
a criminal conviction,

08:42.193 --> 08:45.439
that will only make it easier for the AMA
to take away my medical license.

08:45.439 --> 08:47.010
Well, you're gonna
lose your license, Bob,

08:47.010 --> 08:48.713
–so I wouldn't worry about it.
–Why?

08:48.713 --> 08:51.879
There are many doctors out there prescribing 
medication the FDA hasn't approved for…

08:51.879 --> 08:54.060
Can I stop you?

08:54.060 --> 08:55.921
Don't be self-righteous.
It's annoying.

08:55.921 --> 08:57.603
Sorry I'm late.

08:58.030 --> 09:00.134
What are you doing here?

09:00.134 --> 09:02.331
You asked me to
second chair, Denny. Remember?

09:02.331 --> 09:04.667
–Alan Shore.
–Bob Mclean.

09:04.667 --> 09:05.875
Alan.

09:09.982 --> 09:12.300
–I never asked you to second chair.
–Sure you did, Denny.

09:12.300 --> 09:13.523
You said you were trying the case…

09:13.523 --> 09:15.133
Solo.

09:15.549 --> 09:17.337
I said solo.

09:17.337 --> 09:22.777
Well, I thought you asked for backup,
so I guess one of us is losing our mind.

09:24.945 --> 09:26.855
What do you mean by that?

09:26.855 --> 09:28.373
Denny, I'm here.

09:28.373 --> 09:30.490
As you know, I'm starved
for criminal work.

09:30.490 --> 09:32.969
I want to do this alone.

09:33.695 --> 09:35.575
Is this about proving something?

09:35.575 --> 09:36.989
You said tell Shirley.

09:36.989 --> 09:40.589
Is this about proving to 
Shirley Schmidt you han't slipped?

09:43.022 --> 09:44.454
Excuse me. I'm in a meeting.

09:44.454 --> 09:46.928
Denny, I don't have time
to say this nicely,

09:46.928 --> 09:49.367
so I'm just gonna say it
with all the rough edges.

09:49.367 --> 09:52.615
This is a criminal proceeding.
That man's liberty could be at stake.

09:52.615 --> 09:55.031
I'm jumping in second chair
to cover his ass,

09:55.031 --> 09:57.433
and, yes, possibly yours as well.

10:06.125 --> 10:09.080
Could it be possible she's
doing this for the publicity?

10:09.080 --> 10:11.011
Suing me?

10:11.291 --> 10:13.697
Well, call me a cynic, but 
for two years, you're the it girls.

10:13.697 --> 10:15.958
You're Boston's top publicists.

10:15.958 --> 10:17.458
Business starts to wane,

10:17.458 --> 10:19.633
you leave, she's suddenly
not the flavor of the month.

10:19.633 --> 10:23.720
She sues you, presto, hot copy is
the split girls all over again.

10:23.720 --> 10:26.946
For the cost of attorney and filing fee,
she's featured on every news cast.

10:26.946 --> 10:30.782
As much as she loves the limelight,
Stephanie's honorable.

10:31.119 --> 10:33.365
I wonder.

10:39.077 --> 10:42.072
Is there a reason you keep
looking at me like that?

10:42.072 --> 10:44.328
Like what?

10:45.352 --> 10:47.604
I make you nervous.

10:47.604 --> 10:49.320
You need to get over that.

10:52.823 --> 10:55.247
So how many men 
have you been with?

10:56.311 --> 10:58.169
Why are you asking?

10:59.119 --> 11:01.588
I asked her because she's going 
to be asked on the stand

11:01.588 --> 11:04.352
why she has such a hard time
giving me a straight answer.

11:04.352 --> 11:05.614
However…

11:05.614 --> 11:07.404
It's because…

11:07.404 --> 11:09.764
I have doubts that 
she really is one.

11:09.764 --> 11:11.102
A homosexual.

11:11.102 --> 11:12.629
Yes.

11:12.629 --> 11:15.360
And are these doubts based
on the plaintiff's evidence

11:15.360 --> 11:17.822
or your own scientific compass?

11:20.247 --> 11:22.262
Is she attracted to you, Brad?

11:22.262 --> 11:24.293
She might be.

11:25.791 --> 11:27.411
What?

11:27.411 --> 11:29.070
Why is it men…

11:29.070 --> 11:31.680
I mean, is it the idea of losing
one to the other side,

11:31.680 --> 11:36.004
or is it since you have feelings for her,
you're anxious to believe it's mutual?

11:36.004 --> 11:37.099
You see…

11:37.099 --> 11:40.027
you sucker me with this buddy talk,
get me to reveal my feelings,

11:40.027 --> 11:43.063
and when I do, 
you punish me with them.

11:43.182 --> 11:44.984
I thought you were attracted to me.

11:44.984 --> 11:45.904
You don't want to go there.

11:45.904 --> 11:49.658
Even so, to be forgotten so easily,
and for a homosexual…

11:49.658 --> 11:52.293
is there something taped to 
my forehead that says “mock me”?

11:52.293 --> 11:54.838
Isn't coffee a lovely drug?

11:54.838 --> 11:57.624
I love brain stimulants, don't you?

11:57.961 --> 12:00.389
Uh, Catherine Pipe.

12:00.585 --> 12:02.317
Brad chase.

12:02.317 --> 12:05.963
Brad chase. You're 
defending the lesbian.

12:10.592 --> 12:13.626
Hi. I'm Lori Colson.
We haven't officially met.

12:13.626 --> 12:15.856
Hello, dear. Catherine Piper.

12:15.856 --> 12:21.178
For the future, I don't really 
appreciate comments about my hair.

12:21.178 --> 12:23.735
Oh. I'm sorry.

12:23.735 --> 12:26.214
I was just trying to make conversation,

12:26.214 --> 12:30.460
and I assumed you wouldn't want me
to go anywhere near your eyebrows.

12:39.725 --> 12:42.608
I tried diets, all of them.

12:42.608 --> 12:44.187
I exercised.

12:44.187 --> 12:46.233
I'd gone on fen-phen years ago,

12:46.233 --> 12:48.351
and that helped a little,

12:48.351 --> 12:50.794
but mainly, I just kept getting bigger.

12:50.794 --> 12:54.204
And at some point, the defendant
mentioned a new drug.

12:54.204 --> 12:57.129
Yes. I forgot how he said
he had access to it,

12:57.129 --> 12:59.968
but basically, he said 
he had this new drug,

12:59.968 --> 13:02.388
not on the market yet 
called Ramonibend,

13:02.388 --> 13:06.488
and studies showed how it could
help people lose weight.

13:06.488 --> 13:08.844
Desperate as I was, I just said yes.

13:08.844 --> 13:10.793
He sold you this drug in his office.

13:10.793 --> 13:14.600
Yes, and he told me not to tell anyone

13:14.600 --> 13:17.769
because he said it was illegal
for him to be giving it to me.

13:17.769 --> 13:19.626
Thank you, Mr Harrison.

13:31.148 --> 13:33.374
I can't help but notice
you're really fat.

13:33.374 --> 13:34.507
Yes.

13:34.507 --> 13:36.063
You been fatter? –Much.

13:36.063 --> 13:37.977
Drug worked. –Huge.

13:37.977 --> 13:40.467
I mean, I lost weight,
my cholesterol went down,

13:40.467 --> 13:42.405
my HDL actually went up.

13:42.405 --> 13:44.076
I mean, it was a godsend.

13:44.076 --> 13:45.575
Of course, till the…

13:45.575 --> 13:47.152
you know, 
police cut off my supplier.

13:47.152 --> 13:49.066
Objection to the word 
“supplier,” your honor.

13:49.066 --> 13:50.543
It makes my client sound 
like a drug dealer.

13:50.543 --> 13:52.371
He is a drug dealer.
He sold him drugs.

13:52.371 --> 13:54.581
Yes, but there's a bias that
goes to the word “dealer.”

13:54.581 --> 13:57.853
He simply prescribed him medicine
to help him live.

13:58.438 --> 13:59.459
He's right.

13:59.459 --> 14:01.346
This man almost died.

14:02.178 --> 14:04.711
–Didn't he?
–Didn't you?

14:04.711 --> 14:08.705
I had high blood pressure,
high cholesterol, diabetes.

14:08.705 --> 14:12.355
I mean, I was at serious risk
for a major heart attack or a stroke.

14:12.355 --> 14:13.950
Probably still am.

14:13.950 --> 14:16.685
Since you stopped taking the drug?

14:16.988 --> 14:20.034
I'm having problems again.

14:20.034 --> 14:23.583
Did my client tell you that this
drug is unapproved by the FDA?

14:23.583 --> 14:25.394
Yes.

14:25.394 --> 14:27.234
Did he tell you that, uh,

14:27.234 --> 14:28.896
–there could be side effects?
–Yes.

14:28.896 --> 14:30.315
–You were fully informed.
–I was.

14:30.315 --> 14:31.548
–You consented.
–I did.

14:31.548 --> 14:32.867
–Take it again?
–Absolutely.

14:32.867 --> 14:34.114
–Like the doctor.
–Love him.

14:34.114 --> 14:35.635
–How's your memory?
–My memory's fine.

14:35.635 --> 14:36.990
–What's my name?
–Denny Crane.

14:36.990 --> 14:38.327
–Like you mean it.
–Denny Crane.

14:38.327 --> 14:41.135
–What's my name?
–Denny Crane!

14:41.509 --> 14:42.769
No further questions.

14:48.996 --> 14:51.609
Stephanie Rogers is 
essentially accusing Ms Green

14:51.609 --> 14:53.625
of being a heterosexual 
in sheep's clothing.

14:53.625 --> 14:58.050
If successful, the plaintiff could potentially receive
a judgment in excess of seven figures.

14:58.050 --> 14:59.688
Which is why perhaps…

15:00.477 --> 15:01.842
Wait, she wasn't finished.

15:01.842 --> 15:03.822
Doesn't matter how it's
playing out in public, Tracey.

15:03.822 --> 15:06.651
What matters are the 12 
people in that box.

15:07.840 --> 15:09.333
And?

15:09.333 --> 15:11.674
I can't tell.

15:11.910 --> 15:14.028
Well, you've dated 
more men than women,

15:14.028 --> 15:16.334
so that puts you on the heterosexual
side of the fence.

15:16.334 --> 15:18.245
You certainly could have
been confused, as they said,

15:18.245 --> 15:24.267
but the problem is you're coming 
off as anything but indecisive.

15:25.068 --> 15:28.804
You seem like a woman who knows
exactly what you want.

15:28.804 --> 15:31.974
What is that supposed to mean?

15:32.114 --> 15:34.124
Nothing.

15:37.248 --> 15:40.220
You actually think that 
I'm attracted to you.

15:40.367 --> 15:43.760
I just believe you should be
straight with people.

15:43.760 --> 15:45.177
You know what I mean.

15:45.177 --> 15:47.140
I smell some deceit here.

