20:09.373 --> 20:12.141
–Damn liar.
–I like doing cases with you, Denny.

20:12.141 --> 20:14.361
Can't you just accept that?
It's fun.

20:15.869 --> 20:18.589
Fun, fine.
I'll go with that, then.

20:18.589 --> 20:22.658
You have seemed especially acute.
Are we taking something?

20:23.428 --> 20:28.281
I just rubbed on a little clear cream.
It was just for muscle cramps.

20:29.139 --> 20:31.121
Denny?

20:32.490 --> 20:35.179
Are you taking something?

20:35.982 --> 20:38.262
What I am taking…

20:38.262 --> 20:40.199
is good care of myself.

20:40.199 --> 20:43.451
The old Denny Crane is coming back.

20:53.646 --> 20:56.498
Our business had 
reached sort of a plateau,

20:56.498 --> 20:58.708
and I felt I could do better solo.

20:58.708 --> 21:00.571
And truthfully, I thought
that she might, too.

21:00.571 --> 21:02.925
Now, before leaving, did
you tell your clients?

21:02.925 --> 21:04.524
Absolutely not.

21:04.524 --> 21:09.407
I left, I contacted them, they 
decided to come with me, in that order.

21:09.407 --> 21:11.023
Now, Tracey, 
we've heard the accusation

21:11.023 --> 21:13.735
that you pretended to love 
Stephanie for business reasons.

21:13.735 --> 21:15.646
It's absolutely false.

21:18.121 --> 21:19.771
I fell in love with her.

21:19.771 --> 21:24.753
I mean, the idea that I could 
feign love for 2-plus years just…

21:25.845 --> 21:27.847
you know how much
I loved you, Stephanie.

21:27.847 --> 21:32.003
Ms Green, please do not address 
anyone but me or your counsel.

21:33.871 --> 21:37.232
I never lied to her about 
my sexual orientation,

21:37.232 --> 21:39.006
and I'm offended by that.

21:39.006 --> 21:42.511
How many women had you been with
prior to your relationship with my client?

21:42.511 --> 21:44.734
–Objection.
–Overruled.

21:44.734 --> 21:47.285
However salacious, it's in issue.

21:47.285 --> 21:48.456
How many women?

21:48.456 --> 21:50.251
–One.
–One.

21:50.251 --> 21:52.406
And prior to your relationship 
with my client,

21:52.406 --> 21:54.936
how many men had you had
sexual relationships with?

21:54.936 --> 21:56.765
–Several.
–Several.

21:56.765 --> 21:58.759
–More than five?
–Yes.

21:58.759 --> 22:02.197
–More than 10?
–I wanted to lead a heterosexual life.

22:02.197 --> 22:03.528
Eventually, I realized…

22:03.528 --> 22:05.791
My client asked you
if you were bisexual.

22:05.791 --> 22:08.068
–You answered no.
–Because I'm not.

22:08.068 --> 22:10.468
I may have been 
with men in the past,

22:10.468 --> 22:13.043
but ultimately, I realized
I preferred women.

22:13.043 --> 22:15.739
How many relationships have 
you had since Stephanie?

22:15.739 --> 22:18.327
–One.
–With a man or a woman?

22:18.441 --> 22:20.834
Look, the breakup with Stephanie
was extremely painful.

22:20.834 --> 22:24.420
Your subsequent relationship
was with a man or a woman?

22:24.420 --> 22:26.854
–A man.
–A man.

22:26.854 --> 22:30.752
Now, you spoke earlier about the exact
order of how things went down.

22:30.752 --> 22:32.750
Rewinding a little further back,

22:32.750 --> 22:34.888
you met Stephanie, 
became her lover,

22:34.888 --> 22:37.111
eventually became
her business partner,

22:37.111 --> 22:41.099
left with clients and files,
began having an affair with a man.

22:41.099 --> 22:43.097
Did I get the order right?

22:52.551 --> 22:54.964
I just got destroyed.

22:54.964 --> 22:56.550
Didn't I?

22:56.550 --> 22:58.009
You didn't get destroyed.

22:58.009 --> 23:00.889
It was a tough cross,
but I thought you held up.

23:01.948 --> 23:03.400
Really?

23:03.400 --> 23:05.282
Really.

23:06.643 --> 23:08.964
You know…

23:09.856 --> 23:16.441
to think that I'm straight is to believe
that I'm a profoundly dishonest person.

23:17.929 --> 23:21.512
And I'm not dishonest, Brad.

23:21.538 --> 23:23.842
–Okay.
–You know, I…

23:24.053 --> 23:28.552
I can take you doubting 
my sexual orientation but…

23:28.552 --> 23:30.333
my character, I, uh…

23:30.333 --> 23:31.837
I don't doubt you.

23:36.931 --> 23:40.213
–She's trying to admit something.
–What, that she's not gay?

23:40.213 --> 23:42.495
I don't know. Maybe.

23:43.998 --> 23:46.210
You're making 
a fool of yourself, Brad.

23:46.210 --> 23:47.998
I know when 
I'm being deceived, Tara.

23:47.998 --> 23:50.129
The deception is self-inflicted.

23:50.129 --> 23:53.124
You're infatuated with her,
and you want to believe it's reciprocal.

23:53.124 --> 23:57.224
She's probably more interested
in me than you.

23:57.224 --> 23:59.575
You're making a fool of yourself.

24:02.317 --> 24:04.588
I considered it life or death.

24:04.588 --> 24:07.467
He was at risk of cardiac arrest,
diabetes…

24:07.467 --> 24:09.972
and this drug was your only resort?

24:09.972 --> 24:11.761
It was my last resort.

24:11.761 --> 24:15.895
Believe me, I am not in the habit of
prescribing non-approved drugs, but this…

24:15.895 --> 24:19.426
Doctor, would you tell 
the jury and me, too,

24:19.426 --> 24:21.564
for that matter, because 
I've forgotten.

24:21.564 --> 24:24.170
How Ramonibend works.

24:25.093 --> 24:29.210
It suppresses a protein in the brain
that makes you want to eat.

24:29.210 --> 24:32.321
In fact, this drug blocks
nearly all cravings.

24:32.321 --> 24:36.513
It can be used to help people 
quit smoking, drinking.

24:36.513 --> 24:39.273
Which is why it's been called
the wonder drug.

24:39.273 --> 24:43.064
So you just figured what the hell,
why wait for proof?

24:43.064 --> 24:45.541
My patient couldn't wait, Mr Zale.

24:45.541 --> 24:48.141
He was looking at an imminent
physical demise.

24:48.141 --> 24:50.143
In medical terms, we call it death.

24:50.143 --> 24:52.256
Any published studies on this drug?

24:52.256 --> 24:54.558
To justify this wonder status
you give it.

24:54.558 --> 24:57.098
–Not yet.
–Has this drug been approved for sale?

24:57.098 --> 24:58.355
Not yet.

24:58.355 --> 25:01.115
How'd you get your hands
on this drug, doctor?

25:01.221 --> 25:04.554
I had a connection at one of 
the clinics where it's being tested.

25:04.554 --> 25:06.318
I won't reveal more than that.

25:06.318 --> 25:07.948
You're a licensed doctor

25:07.948 --> 25:11.902
prescribing a drug not approved 
by the FDA to desperate patients.

25:11.902 --> 25:12.938
With a full warning.

25:12.938 --> 25:16.566
How can you warn about a drug 
side effect you don't know about?

25:16.566 --> 25:19.390
The warning that I gave 
Mr Harrison was exactly that.

25:19.390 --> 25:21.209
This drug may have side effects
we don't know about.

25:21.209 --> 25:22.642
Possible fatal side effects.

25:22.642 --> 25:24.577
–There's no evidence of that.
–So you decided…

25:24.577 --> 25:27.503
balancing the benefits against 
the known risk of a coronary

25:27.503 --> 25:30.032
if he doesn't take it,
I favor taking the medication.

25:30.032 --> 25:33.182
–This is an experimental drug.
–Which I have no financial interest in.

25:33.182 --> 25:36.858
–Which you bootlegged.
–My only concern was a patient's health.

25:36.858 --> 25:40.081
So doctors should feel free to
ignore the FDA whenever they choose.

25:40.081 --> 25:42.568
I never said that. –So you should 
feel free whenever you choose.

25:42.568 --> 25:45.457
Sometimes desperate circumstances
require desperate measures.

25:45.457 --> 25:48.908
And desperate people will
do anything, won't they?

26:01.945 --> 26:03.939
Denny.

26:04.765 --> 26:06.714
You're checking 
on me in here, too?

26:06.714 --> 26:08.478
Think I forgot how to piss?

26:08.478 --> 26:09.707
I beg your pardon?

26:09.707 --> 26:11.904
I'm tired of being followed
around like some patient.

26:11.904 --> 26:13.941
I change my underwear every day.
I know how to practice law.

26:13.941 --> 26:16.882
And if you're the one who assigned
Alan Shore to backstop me,

26:16.882 --> 26:18.837
–then you better stop…
–You listen.

26:18.837 --> 26:21.185
–I'm still talking.
–Now I'm talking.

26:21.185 --> 26:25.969
You arrogant old fart,
you have a client facing prison time.

26:25.969 --> 26:28.151
You have no right to exalt your ego.

26:28.151 --> 26:29.327
Don't you talk to me in that…

26:29.327 --> 26:30.910
Shut up!

26:30.910 --> 26:34.118
I am sick of you feeling sorry
for yourself and only yourself.

26:34.118 --> 26:37.397
It was selfish of you
to try this case solo.

26:37.397 --> 26:40.184
Do not start a war with me here.

26:40.184 --> 26:42.349
You may not win it.

26:42.999 --> 26:46.073
That's why you brought Shirley back.

26:46.453 --> 26:48.780
To build an alliance!

26:53.615 --> 26:56.707
Guess you're the one
who forgot how to piss.

27:10.370 --> 27:12.513
Does it smell right to you?

27:12.513 --> 27:16.123
She had a history of men
before my client.

27:16.123 --> 27:20.490
She never hinted to her best friends
that she was anything but heterosexual.

27:20.490 --> 27:24.576
She had an affair with a man
after she left my client.

27:24.576 --> 27:26.601
Her only fling with homosexuality

27:26.601 --> 27:30.711
just happened to coincide with the biggest
financial windfall of her life.

27:30.711 --> 27:32.870
Suddenly being gay got her money,

27:32.870 --> 27:37.850
got her profiled about town
in magazines, on tv, as an it girl.

27:37.850 --> 27:44.113
Newfound fame, newfound money,
newfound sexual orientation.

27:44.821 --> 27:47.932
Does it smell right to you?

27:48.162 --> 27:51.051
In order to make a cause 
of action for fraud,

27:51.051 --> 27:54.849
one must prove that he or she relied on 
the fraud to his or her own detriment.

27:54.849 --> 27:57.315
Now, after partnering with my client,

27:57.315 --> 28:00.796
Ms Rogers' financial and 
professional fortunes soared.

28:00.796 --> 28:01.987
She benefited.

28:01.987 --> 28:04.016
In fact, one might even say,
considering

28:04.016 --> 28:05.612
the media coverage
of this lawsuit,

28:05.612 --> 28:07.685
that she's actually benefiting
from the breakup,

28:07.685 --> 28:11.622
because as any P.R. professional knows,
there's no such thing as bad publicity.

28:11.622 --> 28:14.186
But if you're determined
to get hung up on the issue

28:14.186 --> 28:18.226
is Tracey Green gay or not,
did she really love Stephanie or not,

28:18.226 --> 28:20.811
consider Stephanie's own testimony.

28:20.811 --> 28:24.591
When I asked her 
during the relationship

28:24.591 --> 28:26.933
as she was living it,

28:26.933 --> 28:31.092
did she feel that Tracey loved her?

28:31.092 --> 28:34.738
And she answered yes.

28:34.870 --> 28:37.016
But now in the wake 
of hurt and heartbreak,

28:37.016 --> 28:39.751
she offers a different answer.

28:41.210 --> 28:44.591
Which version do 
you find more reliable?

29:05.968 --> 29:06.975
Anything?

29:06.975 --> 29:09.103
No, they're still deliberating.

29:09.658 --> 29:11.326
–What's this?
–I haven't the slightest idea.

29:11.326 --> 29:14.883
Your secretary said you'd
want it sooner rather than later.

29:17.591 --> 29:19.338
What is it?

29:19.338 --> 29:22.501
It's nothing.
It's just another case I'm working on.

29:39.794 --> 29:44.899
Do I have to convince you of the danger
of prescribing non-approved drugs?

29:44.899 --> 29:50.605
Defrauding overweight people with diet
gimmicks is a billion-dollar industry,

29:50.605 --> 29:54.216
and now we're going to let
doctors get in on the racket

29:54.216 --> 29:58.662
and say it's okay to sell black-market
pills under the table?

29:58.662 --> 30:02.430
It's precisely 
because physicians have

30:02.430 --> 30:04.719
such an influence over their patients

30:04.719 --> 30:09.862
that we demand that drugs 
be approvedby the FDA.

30:09.862 --> 30:15.497
But this doctor decided
he shouldn't be held to that.

30:15.497 --> 30:19.167
This doctor figured 
he's above the law.

30:19.167 --> 30:22.444
This doctor is the equivalent
of a drug dealer

30:22.444 --> 30:25.158
selling cocaine in an alleyway,

30:25.158 --> 30:28.206
and he should be 
punished accordingly.

30:35.501 --> 30:37.142
–I thought I was closing.
–I'm first chair.

30:37.142 --> 30:39.193
–You got to ask all the questions.
–Objection.

30:39.193 --> 30:43.460
Your honor, these two have tried
to trivialize the severity of this case

30:43.460 --> 30:47.577
