to prevent and treat heart attacks.

31:15.198 --> 31:17.792
Did the FDA ever test for that? No.

31:17.792 --> 31:20.552
It was sanctioned only as 
a pain reliever until recently.

31:20.552 --> 31:24.505
Beta-blockers are prescribed
for migraines with no FDA approval.

31:24.505 --> 31:28.134
We take anti-convulsants for pain,
for bipolar disorders.

31:28.134 --> 31:32.087
Antidepressants for insomnia,
steroids for cancer.

31:32.087 --> 31:36.968
People in this country are getting 
prescriptions by the thousands

31:36.968 --> 31:42.290
every day from their doctors for 
treatments the FDA never signed off on.

31:42.290 --> 31:43.787
And what about the FDA?

31:43.787 --> 31:46.448
David Graham, a drug 
reviewer with the agency,

31:46.448 --> 31:50.653
just testified before congress
that the FDA is, I quote,

31:50.653 --> 31:55.611
“virtually incapable of protecting 
America from unsafe drugs.”

31:55.611 --> 31:58.568
The FDA is broken, folks.

31:58.568 --> 32:01.311
Raise your hand if you agree,
except those of you on vioxin.

32:01.311 --> 32:05.375
Objection. –The FDA's 
own point man said to congress

32:05.375 --> 32:10.855
that we are currently facing the 
single greatest drug safety catastrophe

32:10.855 --> 32:12.920
in the history of the world.

32:12.920 --> 32:15.396
So who, then, is there to 
protect the patient?

32:15.396 --> 32:18.872
Who is there to 
protect Mr Harrison?

32:18.872 --> 32:21.193
His doctor.

32:22.106 --> 32:27.764
My client had a medication
that could save his patient's life.

32:27.764 --> 32:35.494
He wasn't going to wait nine years for 
approval from a broken, ineffective agency.

32:35.494 --> 32:38.065
This is life or death, for god's sake.

32:38.065 --> 32:41.881
Life or death.

33:02.180 --> 33:05.121
I'm at risk for Alzheimer's.

33:05.121 --> 33:09.921
I've got some sort of plaque
going on inside my brain.

33:09.921 --> 33:12.384
My memory…

33:12.877 --> 33:16.620
I might have met some of you before.
I wouldn't know.

33:19.617 --> 33:24.062
What you wouldn't know
is what it feels like to be…

33:25.106 --> 33:28.092
losing it, to be…

33:28.092 --> 33:30.912
feel…

33:31.279 --> 33:33.982
to be slipping.

33:39.950 --> 33:44.241
There's a prescription drug…

33:45.475 --> 33:48.794
dextroamphetamine.

33:48.794 --> 33:50.928
It's very big on the black market.

33:50.928 --> 33:55.490
It's used by college kids
to bone up for exams.

33:56.338 --> 33:59.504
I've been taking it.

34:02.079 --> 34:04.602
I don't know how it works,

34:04.602 --> 34:07.035
but you get your memory back.

34:07.035 --> 34:09.496
It reintroduces you
to your vocabulary,

34:09.496 --> 34:15.748
helps with mental arithmetic,
facial recognition, overall productivity.

34:16.906 --> 34:19.585
Basically…

34:19.856 --> 34:22.408
you get your brain back.

